## Foreign Policy and Military Engagement

The attacks triggered a fundamental shift in U.S. foreign policy:

- **The War on Terror:** Initiated immediately after 9/11, this global campaign led to prolonged military engagements in Afghanistan and Iraq, aiming to dismantle terrorist networks and prevent future attacks ([History.com, 2021](https://www.history.com/news/september-11-changes-america)).

- **Intelligence and Counterterrorism:** The U.S. revamped intelligence operations, leading to increased surveillance and cooperation with international partners ([Council on Foreign Relations, 2021](https://www.cfr.org/timeline/how-911-reshaped-foreign-policy)).

- **Long-term Consequences:** Despite initial successes, these wars have been costly and controversial, with critiques comparing them to Vietnam in terms of overcommitment and limited strategic gains ([AFSA, 2021](https://afsa.org/america-and-911-real-world-impact-terrorism-and-extremism)).

